⭐ DOCUMENT 4 — Safe Use Guide for the IP Continuity Watermark (Corrected + Final)
Title:
Safe Use Guide for the IP Continuity Watermark

Body:
The IP Continuity Watermark is a public‑safe badge designed to help creators signal authorship, establish continuity, and 
participate in a global, creator‑driven protection network.

By using this graphic even once, you are declaring that:
you want your creative work to be protected through the compounding power of continuity, and
By using this watermark, you voluntarily choose to have your watermarked work recognized as part of the public continuity 
layer. You do not need to upload anything to the public vault — the act of using the graphic itself signifies that you want 
your work wrapped in continuity‑based protection. From the moment you post or display the graphic, you are declaring your 
intent to contribute your work to the growing collection of continuity‑protected creations through the compounding effects 
of the IP Legacy System.

Using the badge automatically places the marked work into the public continuity perimeter, meaning it is treated as 
publicly declared, timestamped, and continuity‑anchored through the VaultForge‑Live ecosystem.

No upload is required.
The act of use is the act of declaration.

How to Use the Watermark Safely
Download the badge.

